	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This spell does indeed cause you to lose stamina, and quite rapidly at that.  I got a little firsthand experience with that using bind sight to get a feel for the inside of Unrest.  Needless to say, I watched and watched and watched, and when the fellow who's eyes I was looking through pulled a big train to the zone, I was the last one through, due to my incredibly low stamina.<BR>
<BR>
I've also used the spell on creatures who were looking at me, and then using my &quot;hide&quot; skill.  It's one way to know for sure.<BR>
<BR>
I've never had this spell wear off, ever, and I've used it for extended periods of time.  I once cast it on a fish, then climbed out of the water and went fishing, just to see if it was possible to catch the fish I used bind sight on.  Didn't work though, not that I expected it too.<BR>
<BR>
The person who said this spell had no range limit is correct.  I can select a person in my group from the box in the upper-right of the screen, cast the spell and be binded to them.  It's a fun spell, and for some reason your teammates like you to bind to them while they explore or fight.  I don't exactly understand it at all, unless they want you to see firsthand just how fearless they are.<BR>
<BR>
My last trick for this spell is kind of a mean one, I sometimes play in newbie zones.  I give skeletons a Qeynos kite shield and a decent FS weapon.  Then I hit them with every buff I've got.  I cast bind sight on them, and watch the hijinks as a greedy low-level charges this skeleton that should be quite weak, but is instead very unexplainably strong.<BR>
<BR>
My favorite little pet killed, yes, actually killed, three people before someone tried to pull him to the guards.  I killed him myself, and retrieved the items to store in the bank until the next time I want a good laugh.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
