	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				My experience Bind Sight is that it is never resisted and is not considered an offensive spell.  However you can cast it on anything in the zone regardless of how close you are to the creature.  I tested this in the Oasis of Marr while standing on P1.  I cast it on the first person running by and watched through their eyes as they ran toward P2.  As he approached P2 I selected a croc (mind you I never actually moved from P1) and cast.  I jumped into the Croc until someone started attacking it and jumped into him.  From there I jumped from person/creature to person/creature all around the zone.<BR>
<BR>
Now.  Where I figure this would have some serious usefulness is in a dungeon.  Your group is standing at a corner guarded and cannot see around?  Just bind sight onto of the MOBs at the corner and then you could not only check out the situation there but actually jump from MOB to MOB down the hall/corridor whatever to do a little recon and scout out what might lie ahead.<BR>
<BR>
To me this spell has uses that go way beyond simple parlor tricks.  Try it out.  Might find it to be of almost invaluable use in the right instances.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
